manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Fall in love with our award winning WubbaNub Pacifier, the original part plush, part pacifier. The patented WubbaNub design is sure to be your baby’s first friend. The unique style of the original WubbaNub Pacifier allows it to remain near baby’s mouth, easy to grasp, nearly impossible to lose and may assist baby to self soothe. WubbaNub is distributed in hospitals, NICU and well-baby units nationwide and is made with a 100% silicone pacifier, a non-latex and BPA, PVC and Phthalate-free. The durable one-piece construction of the pacifier means no germs hiding between cracks. WubbaNub is a safety-first company that mandates all infant/baby products are completely safety tested. NOTE: WubbaNub Pacifiers purchased online are packaged in a clear polybag with header card that further describes features and benefits.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars So far so good
reviews.reviewText: We got this and the frog for our newborn. His sister had the giraffe when she was a baby. The frog and giraffe are a bit easier for the baby to use since their bodies are longer and lay flat; this one, while super cute, is a bit bulbous so it doesn’t stay still as much.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 1, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cute and they work!
reviews.reviewText: Love these! I’ve bought so many wabbanubs and love them! The different characters make it fun for your little one. I like the bigger ones for the younger ages because it’s easier to grasp. Also! My original plan was to not use pacifiers but after we introduced my daughter it was such a life saver! Also to clean I just throw them in the washer machine / dryer and then give the pacifier part a rinse off because lint gets stuck on it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 5, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars It’s a pacifier
reviews.reviewText: My baby doesn’t like it. He doesn’t like pacifiers at all, instead prefers to suck on his blanket (which is freakin gross) my older kid use to love these pacifiers when she was a baby. She had like 5 wubanubs specifically, which is why I got some for my baby, but he’s a blanket sucker so 🤷🏼‍♀️

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 23, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My daughter's favorite!
reviews.reviewText: My daughter has probably about 10 Wubanub pacifiers. But, when I saw the Narwhal, we had to have it for her. It's adorable and much cuter than what the pictures show. When, we got it in the mail, my daughter was soooo happy. (She's almost a year old.)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 27, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My son’s absolute favorite!
reviews.reviewText: This has become my son’s absolute favorite pacifier! He rubs its little flippers and chooses it over all his other pacifiers

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2021
reviews.reviewText: My newest child loves it! We call him Nelson (The Narwhal) as we have Wilber (the elephant) for the oldest child. It is soft and squishy for them to hold. It's really nice for them to be able to hold something with the nuk.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Cute and cuddly
reviews.reviewText: Great product, taking off one star because the pacifier really should be removable to be able to wash/sanitize

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 27, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Adorable, use it all the time, easy to keep track of
reviews.reviewText: Bought this for my son. He uses it all the time. I love Wubbanub products so they are a must have item for my kids.. It's very cute and soft.. and hard to lose.
